    @Public
public interface FlatMapFunction<T,O>
extends Function, java.io.Serializable
    Base interface for flatMap functions. FlatMap functions take elements and transform them, into zero, one, or more elements. Typical applications can be splitting elements, or unnesting lists and arrays. Operations that produce multiple strictly one result element per input element can also use the MapFunction.

    The basic syntax for using a FlatMapFunction is as follows: 

    
 DataSet<X> input = ...;
 
 DataSet<Y> result = input.flatMap(new MyFlatMapFunction());

        void flatMap(T value,
             Collector<O> out)
      throws java.lang.Exception
        The core method of the FlatMapFunction. Takes an element from the input data set and transforms it into zero, one, or more elements.
        参数:
        value - The input value.
        out - The collector for returning result values.
        抛出:
        java.lang.Exception - This method may throw exceptions. Throwing an exception will cause the operation to fail and may trigger recovery.
